{"id": 243346760, "title": "Biden and Trump battle for blue-collar voters as steel merger looms", "text": "Pittsburgh - Working class voters in Rust Belt cities like Pittsburgh used to favor Democrats overwhelmingly, but years of economic hardship and the rise of social issues favoring Republicans have made them a swing constituency again in 2024.U.S. President Joe Biden has cleared one key hurdle, winning endorsements from union presidents, including the United Steelworkers (USW), a key player in the U.S. Steel takeover battle that has loomed over the 2024 campaign in Pennsylvania.But just how many rank-and-file workers ignore union chiefs and vote for Donald Trump could have a decisive impact in Pennsylvania, Michigan and Wisconsin, where the margin could be 100,000 votes or fewer.", "summary": "Just how many rank-and-file workers ignore union chiefs and vote for Donald Trump could have a decisive impact in Pennsylvania, Michigan and Wisconsin.", "url": "https://www.japantimes.co.jp/business/2024/06/29/biden-trump-blue-collar-workers-steel/", "image": "https://www.japantimes.co.jp/japantimes/uploads/images/2024/06/29/406294.JPG", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-29 06:02:24", "author": "John Biers,Web Master", "authors": ["John Biers", "Web Master"], "language": "en", "source_country": "jp", "sentiment": -0.094}